korean:
  title: 두
  author: 성현
  language: kor
  text: |-
    기장 한 알을 보탬으로써 만종도 시작 되고
    한 푼을 더함으로써 백성이 곤하나니
    규촬을 신중히 하고
    백성과 이권을 다투지 말라
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1470_040_0030&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Measure
  author: Sung Hyun
  language: eng
  text: |-
    A single grain of millet added builds toward ten thousand measures.
    One more portion taken leaves the people exhausted.
    Be cautious with what you measure and collect—
    do not contend with your people for profit.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The poem employs the image of grain measurement as a metaphor for taxation and administrative collection from the people.
  - key: ''
    value: 規撮 (gyukchwal) refers to the careful measurement and collection of taxes, traditionally symbolizing administrative responsibility.
